<h2 id="questions" class="mb-5">FAQ</h2>

<h3 class="h5" id="new-validator">How to become a validator?</h3>
<p class="mb-5">
  Please take a look at this detailed guide on Solana website:
  <%= link_to "https://docs.solana.com/running-validator", "https://docs.solana.com/running-validator" %>.
</p>

<h3 class="h5" id="personal-data">How is my Personal Data protected?</h3>
<p class="mb-5">
  All Consumer Personal Information is encrypted in transit via HTTPS. You can see our secure certificate by
  clicking the lock icon in your browser location bar. We also encrypt all Personal Information at rest when it is
  stored within our database.
</p>

<h3 class="h5" id="private-validator">Why is my validator marked "private"?</h3>
<p class="mb-5">
  It's based on commission rate. 100% commission means that you are not looking for delegations, so we mark you
  as "private". Private validators are always assigned with total score 0, despite their performance.
</p>

<h3 class="h5" id="withdraw-authority-warning">
  Why do I see <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle text-warning mx-1"></i> warning next to my validator?
</h3>
<p class="mb-5">
  It informs visitors that your validator identity matches the withdraw authority on your vote account. It is
  a serious security risk, eg. if someone hacks into your validator, they can steal from the vote account.
  Keep the withdraw authority key offline to minimize the risk. Once you fix it, the warning will be
  taken off automatically within few hours.
</p>

<h3 class="h5" id="admin-warning">
  Why do I see <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle text-danger mx-1"></i> warning next to my validator?
</h3>
<p class="mb-5">
  It informs visitors that validator's actions are malicious or harmful to the cluster. Hover your mouse over
  the warning symbol next to validator's name to see the details. Validators with red warnings are always
  assigned with total score 0, despite their performance.
</p>

<h3 class="h5" id="avatar">How can I change my avatar (validator logo)?</h3>
<p class="mb-5">
  The images come from the validator's Keybase profile. Once you change it on Keybase, we'll update avatar in our
  system automatically within 24 hours.
</p>


<h3 class="h5" id="investing">How do I start investing?</h3>
<p class="mb-5">
  First, you'll need some SOLs. You can buy them on <%= link_to "Coinbase", "https://www.coinbase.com/" %>. Then send
  them to your web wallet, such as <%= link_to "Phantom", "https://phantom.app/" %> or
  <%= link_to "Solflare", "https://solflare.com/" %>. For other options check out
  <%= link_to "Solana web wallets", "https://docs.solana.com/wallet-guide/web-wallets" %> or
  <%= link_to "Solana mobile wallets", "https://docs.solana.com/wallet-guide/apps" %>. You are ready to stake! To learn
  more about staking see <%= link_to "Solana staking docs", "https://docs.solana.com/staking" %>. Then check out
  our advice on <%= link_to "how to choose the right validator", "#choosing-validator" %>.
</p>

<h3 class="h5" id="best-validator">How to find the best validator?</h3>
<p class="mb-5">
  To find a good validator, please start at the top of the 'Score' view on the home page and click through
  to see validator details. Then read <%= link_to "Choosing Validator", "#choosing-validator" %> section on this
  page to find out what you should watch out for.
</p>

<h3 class="h5" id="change-validator">How often can I change the validator? Is there a minimum period?</h3>
<p class="mb-5">
  It usually takes 1 epoch for stake to warm up or cool down. Try to split your stake across several validators. Please
  also read our advice on <%= link_to "how to choose the right validator", "#choosing-validator" %> and check out Solana
  <%= link_to "stake pool", "https://spl.solana.com/stake-pool/overview" %> program.
</p>

<h3 class="h5" id="staking-rewards">How often are the staking rewards paid out?</h3>
<p class="mb-5">
  It usually takes 1 epoch for stake to warm up or cool down. After that, you should see rewards in your wallet. For
  better results, try to split your stake across several validators. Please also read our advice on
  <%= link_to "how to choose the right validator", "#choosing-validator" %> or check out Solana
  <%= link_to "stake pool", "https://spl.solana.com/stake-pool/overview" %> program.
</p>

<h3 class="h5" id="apy">Where can I find the APY?</h3>
<p class="mb-5">
  We do not show APY on validators.app. See <%= link_to "https://www.stakeview.app", "https://www.stakeview.app" %>
  for a good look at APY.
</p>
